# Data Fetching

Next.js provides multiple patterns for loading data, from server-side fetching in components to client-side hooks.

## Server Components (App Router — Recommended)

Server Components can fetch data directly with async/await. No special APIs needed.

### fetch API

```tsx
// app/posts/page.tsx
export default async function PostsPage() {
  const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com/posts')
  const posts = await res.json()

  return (
    <ul>
      {posts.map((post: { id: string; title: string }) => (
        <li key={post.id}>{post.title}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  )
}
```

### Database / ORM

```tsx
// app/users/page.tsx
import { db } from '@/lib/db'

export default async function UsersPage() {
  const users = await db.user.findMany()
  return (
    <ul>
      {users.map(user => (
        <li key={user.id}>{user.name}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  )
}
```

### Parallel Fetching

```tsx
export default async function DashboardPage() {
  // Start both requests simultaneously
  const statsPromise = getStats()
  const activityPromise = getActivity()

  // Wait for both
  const [stats, activity] = await Promise.all([statsPromise, activityPromise])

  return (
    <div>
      <StatsPanel stats={stats} />
      <ActivityFeed activity={activity} />
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Sequential Fetching

```tsx
export default async function ArtistPage({ params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }) {
  const { id } = await params
  const artist = await getArtist(id) // Fetch first
  const albums = await getAlbums(artist.id) // Then fetch dependent data

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{artist.name}</h1>
      <AlbumList albums={albums} />
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Caching

Next.js extends the `fetch` API with caching options:

```tsx
// Cached by default (equivalent to force-cache)
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data')

// No caching — always fresh
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data', {
  cache: 'no-store',
})

// Time-based revalidation (seconds)
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data', {
  next: { revalidate: 3600 }, // Revalidate every hour
})

// Tag-based revalidation
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data', {
  next: { tags: ['posts'] },
})
```

### Route Segment Config

```tsx
// Force dynamic rendering for the entire route
export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'

// Set default revalidation for all fetches in this segment
export const revalidate = 60 // seconds

// Force static rendering
export const dynamic = 'force-static'
```

## Revalidation

### Time-Based

```tsx
// Revalidate cached data every 60 seconds
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data', {
  next: { revalidate: 60 },
})
```

### On-Demand

```tsx
// In a Server Action or Route Handler
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache'
import { revalidateTag } from 'next/cache'

export async function updatePost() {
  await db.post.update(...)

  revalidatePath('/blog')         // Revalidate a specific path
  revalidateTag('posts')          // Revalidate all fetches with this tag
}
```

## Streaming with Suspense

Wrap slow data-fetching components in Suspense to stream them progressively:

```tsx
import { Suspense } from 'react'

export default function DashboardPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Dashboard</h1>
      {/* Shows instantly */}
      <StaticContent />

      {/* Streams in when data is ready */}
      <Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
        <SlowDataComponent />
      </Suspense>

      <Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
        <AnotherSlowComponent />
      </Suspense>
    </div>
  )
}

async function SlowDataComponent() {
  const data = await fetchSlowAPI() // Takes 2 seconds
  return <DataDisplay data={data} />
}
```

### loading.tsx (Automatic Suspense)

```tsx
// app/dashboard/loading.tsx
export default function Loading() {
  return <DashboardSkeleton />
}
// Next.js wraps the page in <Suspense fallback={<Loading />}> automatically
```

## Static Generation (generateStaticParams)

```tsx
// app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx
export async function generateStaticParams() {
  const posts = await getAllPosts()
  return posts.map(post => ({ slug: post.slug }))
}

export default async function PostPage({ params }: { params: Promise<{ slug: string }> }) {
  const { slug } = await params
  const post = await getPost(slug)
  return <article><h1>{post.title}</h1></article>
}
```

## Client-Side Fetching

### SWR

```tsx
'use client'
import useSWR from 'swr'

const fetcher = (url: string) => fetch(url).then(r => r.json())

export default function UserProfile() {
  const { data, error, isLoading } = useSWR('/api/user', fetcher)

  if (isLoading) return <div>Loading...</div>
  if (error) return <div>Error</div>
  return <div>Hello, {data.name}</div>
}
```

### React `use` API

```tsx
// Pass promise from Server Component to Client Component
// app/page.tsx (Server)
import { Suspense } from 'react'
import ClientList from './client-list'

export default function Page() {
  const dataPromise = fetchData() // Don't await!
  return (
    <Suspense fallback={<div>Loading...</div>}>
      <ClientList dataPromise={dataPromise} />
    </Suspense>
  )
}

// app/client-list.tsx (Client)
'use client'
import { use } from 'react'

export default function ClientList({ dataPromise }: { dataPromise: Promise<Item[]> }) {
  const data = use(dataPromise)
  return <ul>{data.map(item => <li key={item.id}>{item.name}</li>)}</ul>
}
```

## Pages Router Data Fetching

| Method | When | Use Case |
|--------|------|----------|
| `getStaticProps` | Build time (+ ISR) | Blog, marketing, products |
| `getServerSideProps` | Every request | Dashboards, auth pages |
| `getStaticPaths` | Build time | Dynamic routes with SSG |
| Client-side (SWR) | Browser | User-specific, real-time |

See [[nextjs/pages-router]] for detailed Pages Router data fetching examples.

## Decision Guide

| Scenario | Approach |
|----------|----------|
| Public page, rarely changes | Static (default in App Router) |
| Public page, changes hourly | Time-based revalidation (`next: { revalidate: 3600 }`) |
| User-specific data, server-rendered | Server Component with no cache |
| User-specific data, interactive | Client-side with SWR |
| Multiple independent data sources | Parallel `Promise.all()` |
| Dependent data sources | Sequential with Suspense boundaries |
| Large page, mixed fast/slow data | Streaming with `<Suspense>` |
